doc.after: Brummie sometimes Brummy is a colloquial term for the inhabitants accent and dialect of Birmingham England as well as being a general adjective used to denote a connection with the city locally called Brum The terms are all derived from Brummagem or Bromwichham historical variants or alternatives to Birmingham
